| history        = * Demons previously had a chance to drop [[Magic Sword]]s and [[Coconut]]s, but this is no longer the case.
* With [[Updates/7.0|Update 7.0]], its [[HP]] was raised from 5,500 HP to 8,200.
* With [[Updates/10.37|Update 10.37]], it no longer drops [[Double Axe]]s.
* As announced on {{OfficialNewsArchive|8284|March 04, 2025}}, the [[Updates/14.12.5229e4|patch]] reduced the drop rate of [[Might Ring]] for this creature, thus changing its rarity from '''semi-rare''' to '''rare'''.

==== Mintwallin Spawn ====
[[File:Daemon.gif|left]] The first Demon appeared near present-day [[Mintwallin]], south of the current city, and was significantly weaker than its modern counterpart. It was removed in an update between 1999 and 2000. Originally named '''Daemon''', it retained this name until [[Updates/5.1|Update 5.1]] and had a slightly different appearance.

This [[Daemon]] had 3,000 HP and granted 6,000 experience points. It resided on a level above [[Cavern City]], south of [[Mintwallin]]. Initially, Daemons were pushable and could be trapped using items like [[Parcel]]s and [[Flower Pot]]s. Players around level 30 could kill them.

The '''Daemon''' was inspired by the '''Ethereal Monster''' from ''Ultima VII''.

==== Demons Return to Tibia ====
[[File:Demon (6.0).gif|left]] When [[Edron]] was introduced, Demons became available again, but only to players with a [[Premium Account]]. They received a new sprite, closely resembling their current appearance. 
